assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Musashi Co., Ltd. provides information/industrial, printing, cash handling, and election systems equipment in Japan and internationally. It offers media conversion services to digitalize documents and microfilms; data input services; and information processing services, include production of microfilm images. The company also engages in the consultation and sale of scanners, electronic archive systems, electronic document systems and other information products, as well as industrial non-destructive inspection systems for buildings and manufactured products; manufacture and sale of thermal enlarger printers and thermal papers; and development and sale of image processing software. In addition, it consults and sells printing equipment, materials, and software for digital pre-press systems and print-on-demand systems, and laser systems; and develops and sells a compact print-on-demand system for business cards, tickets, as well as provides maintenance services for equipment. Further, the company offers cash handling machines for various industries, such as finance, retail, courier, transport, and amusement under the tellac name; security products, including administrative products for keys; and exports cash handling machines, including bill counters and bill binding machines to international markets. Additionally, it provides election systems equipment comprising ballot paper dispensers, counters, reader sorters, issuers, self-opening ballot papers, administrative software, promotional items, and other tools; and various types of paper and paperboards for printing, publishing, information, special paper, office paper, cardboard, as well as processed paper products. Furthermore, the company engages in the real estate and auto leasing, as well as insurance brokerage activities. Musashi Co., Ltd. was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan.
